{{Quote|I entered the restaurant and found the place trashed. Many of the patrons were under the tables or running for the exits. A humanoid male, approximate 1.7 meters in height, with scarred features, seemed to be trying to calm a large Aqualish, who lunged forward with a punch that sent the humanoid flying. He landed on the floor next to me.|Kras'ka Lo'lar on Ponda Baba and Cornelius Evazan in Report 056.239|<ref name="EGAS">[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species (real-world book)|''The Essential Guide to Alien Species'']]</ref>}}
'''Kras'ka Lo'lar''' was an individual who served in the security [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|police]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Bothawui/Legends|Bothawui]]. At some point between [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]] and [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]], the officer encountered the [[Aqualish/Legends|Aqualish]] [[Ponda Baba/Legends|Ponda Baba]] trashing a [[Restaurant/Legends|restaurant]], ending when Lo'lar stunned Baba. A report of the incident was included in ''[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species]]'', a guidebook with media acquired by [[Senior Anthropologist]] [[Mammon Hoole]].

==Biography==
{{Quote|Why did you have to shoot him? He's an Aqualish, small things upset him.''"</br>"''What 'small thing' set this off?''"</br>"''I'd just told him that he's going to have to wait to get his arm fixed. He didn't like that very much.|A conversation between Cornelius Evazan and Kras'ka Lo'lar as detailed in Report 0.56.239|<ref name="EGAS" />}} 
[[File:PondaBaba-BaseSeries4.png|thumb|right|250px|Kras'ka Lo'lar stunned Ponda Baba (pictured) on Bothawui.]]
A security [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|police]] officer on the [[Planet/Legends|world]] [[Bothawui/Legends|Bothawui]], Kras'ka Lo'lar worked<ref name="EGAS" /> sometime between [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]] to [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]]. In that [[Time/Legends|time]],<ref name="Date">[[Ponda Baba/Legends|Ponda Baba's]] [[Limb/Legends|arm]] is removed in {{Film|IV}}, the events of which are set in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]] per ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''. Baba gains a cybernetic arm in ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', which is set from [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] to [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]] per the reasoning [[Template:SWG timeline|here]].</ref> Lo'lar entered a [[Restaurant/Legends|restaurant]] getting trashed by the [[Aqualish/Legends|Aqualish]] [[Ponda Baba/Legends|Ponda Baba]] as the establishment's patrons ran. Baba's partner,<ref name="EGAS" /> Doctor [[Cornelius Evazan/Legends|Cornelius Evazan]]<ref name="CE">''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia]]''</ref> tried to calm him, but the Aqualish punched him, throwing the doctor over to floor next to Lo'lar. The police officer set their [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] on stun and dispatched Baba with two shots. Running back to the Aqualish, Evazan gave Lo'lar a look of disgust, and asked why they shot him, reasoning that small things upset him as an Aqualish. Lo'lar asked the doctor what uspet him, and Evazan revealed that he had just told Baba that he had to wait on getting his [[Limb/Legends|arm]] fixed. Examining the Aqualish more closely, Lo'lar realized that Baba had only one arm, and the other was prosthetic.<ref name="EGAS" />

Lo'lar reported on the incident in a work titled [[Report 056.239]]. The report was used by [[Senior Anthropologist]] Mammon Hoole, alongside various other collected media, for in the book ''[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species]]'', a guide on [[Alien/Legends|aliens]] published with the help of a [[Ann Margaret Lewis|professional writer]] in the time of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] during or after [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]]. The report was included in the Aqualish section of the guidebook.<ref name="EGAS" />

==Equipment==
{{Quote|I set my blaster on stun and fired at the Aqualish. It took two shots to take him down. He stumbled and fell to the floor.|Kras'ka Lo'lar in Report 056.239|<ref name="EGAS" />}}
Lo'lar used a blaster to stun Ponda Baba.<ref name="EGAS" />

==Behind the scenes==
Kras'ka Lo'lar was introduced in the [[2001]] reference book ''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]'', written by [[Ann Margaret Lewis (real person)|Ann Margaret Lewis]].<ref name="EGAS" />

